<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I agree with the weapon choice. When you can afford it (60-90pp) get your hands on a dragoon dirk if you plan to stay with a piercing weapon, otherwise start with a cracked staff. I advise to stay away from 2 handed weapons because you will want to hold some item in your off hand that provides additional mana or intelligence. At levels 16+ you will probably not use a weapon any more since to melee hurts real bad; your pet will do all the tanking for you. If you start a High Elf or Gnome, you can easily get cloth armor from the orcs in Greater Faydark. Soon as money permits, you will need to step up to Raw Silk armor, because you will still need to melee until level 16 and raw silk will be the best affordable armor until you reach that level. If you start a Dark Elf, you will not find much in the way of cloth armor dropping from mobs in Nektulos Forest or in East Commons; the orcs in Greater Faydark drop armor far more frequently from my experience. Almost any race can wear the armor that any magician can wear (I said almost). Dark ELfs look great in a red magician rob. When time and money permits, pick up jewelry that adds mana. Do not worry about intelligence jewelry until you reach level 16, though the higher the intelligence, the faster your skills will go up. Your pet stinks at low levels, so you need to do most of the fighting and nuking, so the extra mana helps. When you create your character , dump all available points into intelligence. do NOT create a human.<P>
</FONT>
