<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Human mage here.<P>For a mage, not much matters but your brain.  You get the same pet as I do whether you have 100 int or 200, and pets are your main strength.<P>I think humans are fun to play, you get heatstone at 16 anyway.  Go for AC and AGI after putting modest points into Int.  Mages get a spell that regens HP so stepping up and taking some hits is a good way to become more efficient.  I used to love it when I stepped up and MISS, MISS, DODGE, MISS due to my 97 agi.  All the while the pet is smashing it to bits.<P>My starting INT was 105 as a human and it never made much of a difference.  I still have only 176 int at lvl 54 and I just don't go OOM that much.<P>PS  Got my wife hooked and she made a mage and I made a monk.  Lovin it.
