<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Being a human mage will hurt a LOT in higher level encounters, but if you never plan on doing those, then choose whatever you want.<P>Reasoning:<P>The only stat you should be worried about is int, once you hit 200 keep trying to find higher int gear to get some more of the important stuff...resist gear.<P>After level 45 or so, your resists play a MAJOR role in your defense, and a mage with low resists is a mage that dies a LOT.  So, if you start with higher int, it is easier to get to 200, and thus easier to get yourself a lot of high resist gear.<P>Humans suck, high elfs are decent, erudites and dark elves are pointless, gnomeys are the way to go.
</FONT>
